Singapore Ruling Party to Release Manifesto, Straits Times Says

-- B y   K a t r i n a   N i c h o l a s
-- 
2011-04-17T01:14:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-17/singapore-ruling-party-to-release-manifesto-straits-times-says.html
Singapore ’s ruling People’s Action
Party will release its manifesto today ahead of the country’s
upcoming general elections, the  Straits Times  reported, citing
Deputy Prime Minister Teo Chee Hean.  The city-state faces an uncertain world and must prepare
itself with policies, programs and a political system that can
take in a range of alternative views, the newspaper cited him as
saying. The PAP completed its introduction of 24 new candidates
last week, the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story: Katrina Nicholas in
Singapore at   knicholas2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Tighe at   ptighe@bloomberg.net  